 JOHANNESBURG - It’s time for the Gauteng education department to pay back the money. The Special Tribunal has set aside its contracts for deep cleaning at schools amid the fight against COVID-19. READ: KZN Education Department waiting for mobile classrooms The Special Tribunal found that the department did not follow procedures in awarding the contracts worth over R400m. The Special Investigating Unit will now recover the profits made by the contracted service providers. The SIU approached the tribunal to review and set aside the contracts after it discovered that hundreds of millions were paid. Investigations revealed that companies were appointed without verification or checking whether they appeared on the government's Central Supplier Database. Read the Special Investigating Unit statement below: Media Statement - Gauteng Education Contracts Set Aside 11 Feb 2022 by eNews Channel Africa on Scribd 